free_txt: Letter
FN Pelletron tandem accelerator
The target thickness was monitored by comparing
yields relative to 197Au(alpha,alpha)197Au, and showed
that targets experienced an increase of 10%-40% in
thickness over time. Corrections for the target
thickness growth were applied in the analysis.
Richard James deBoer (2013-02-15):
Note that the order of data is VERY important as some
of the data points have the same energy. There are
the same number of data points at every angle as the
data were taken simultaneously with 32 silicon
detectors.
An array of 32 ion-implanted silicon detectors
(100 um thickness, 100 mm2 area) were arranged at a
distance of 63 cm from the target at the center of a
vacuum chamber.
FN Pelletron tandem accelerator
200 nA of highly collimated 4He2+ beam on carbon
target foils
FWHM(beam)=5 keV at 5.2473(21)MeV resonance
Corrected for equilibrium charge state of beam

Rutherford cross section corrected for screening
effect correction (1-5%).
The thickness of Au layer (0.22-1.79 ug/cm2) was
constant during the course of experiment.
Nine natural carbon targets were used, each with a
thin (0.2-2 ug/cm2) layer of evaporated Au and carbon
thicknesses of 11-25 ug/cm2.
The targets were oriented at a 45 deg angle relative to
incident beam.
Richard James deBoer (2013-02-16):
I believe the uncertainty is purely statistical.
The data at the 32 angles were measured simultaneously
at a given energy, one can take the ratio of their
yields and this approximates the ratio in the cross
sections.
